The paper discusses the development of a more efficient distributed data processing framework for frequent itemset mining (FIM) algorithms, which is a common task in database systems (cs.DB). The paper also focuses on the use of parallel computing to improve the efficiency of FIM algorithms, which falls under the category of distributed and parallel computing (cs.Distributed and Parallel Computing). The use of in-memory computation and resilient distributed dataset (RDD) features in the Spark framework is also discussed, which is related to data management and storage (cs.DC). The paper proposes a parallel Eclat algorithm on the Spark RDD framework, which is a data mining algorithm and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
